Our Staff
Meet the Family
The Town and Country RV Resort is family owned and operated by the Hawkins family since 2000.
Steve Hawkins
OWNER/MAINTENANCE MANAGER
Steve has worked in the RV and Mobile Home business for 55 years, since 1968. He excels at maintaining the park property, continuously improving the facilities and roads and always finds new varieties of plants, trees and bamboo to add to the landscaping.
Mary Hawkins
OFFICE MANAGER
Mary has worked in the RV and Mobile Home business for 47 years, since 1976. She is very knowledgeable about the Dade City area and can provide numerous ideas to residents looking to take day trips around Florida.
David Hawkins
PARK MAINTENANCE
David has worked in the RV and Mobile Home business for 39 years, since 1984, when he began accompanying his father to the parts store at the age of 5. He works with his father daily, trimming trees, laying blacktop, maintaining the pool or painting the community buildings. He is an avid mountain biker and also enjoys working with metal.
Kim Hawkins
WEB PRESENCE & SOCIAL MEDIA MARKETING
Kim has helped out with the website design and content since 2008 and also posts about park news and events related to Town & Country RV Resort on the
Facebook
and
Instagram
pages.
We work hard every day so you can safely enjoy your retirement years.
Come Stay With Us
All Town & Country RV sites are full hook-up and have either 30 or 50 amp service (50 amp available on all sites).  All of our sites are very spacious at 75 feet long and we have no limitations on RV length. Pull through lots in the back can house RVs pulling trailers.

About Town & Country
OUR RESORT
About Us
Town and Country RV Resort is a seasonal 55+ community located four miles north of downtown Dade City amidst the rolling hills and Spanish moss covered oaks of Western Central Florida. We made it our goal to provide an RV resort that is well-maintained, enjoyable and beautiful for our guests.
Family-owned and operated
35 shaded acres of land
COMMUNITY
Our History
The Town and Country RV Resort was built in 1986. The Hawkins family purchased the Town and Country RV Resort in 2000, and the resort continues to be family owned and operated. Our 55+ R.V. resort is situated on 35 acres, complete with a driving range and pool. We work hard every day so you can safely enjoy your retirement years.
Our Staff
Our Lovely RV Resort in Dade City, FL
Our little spot nestled on a hill in the lovely Florida countryside will offer you days full of activities, a strong sense of community, and companionship with your neighbors.
Sunshine
Sunshine is a great part of our focus here; dip in our relaxing heated pool or enjoy a walk on the 35 acres. Early risers will be able to catch sights of the most amazing birds in the area. Some refer to our park as a tropical oasis.
Recreational Hall
Our recreational hall offers books and puzzles for some independent entertainment or our social clubs host everything from shuffleboard tournaments, bingo, euchre, bridge, to dinners and dances. The fun is all here, you decide how much to have.
Animals
We have 13 open space acres in the rear of the park for dog-walking or exercising. Even if you don’t own an animal, you can spend a few restful moments saying hello to Susie, Wifi, Snowy and Baby, the Town & Country feline mascots.
Prime Location
Located in Dade City, only 5 miles from the nearest grocery stores, antiques shops, pharmacies, shopping centers and hospitals. We offer a country, slow-paced feel but provides residents the necessary amenities close to home. Tampa is less than an hour drive and Orlando is just over an hour away.
Relaxation Paradise
Enjoy your days relaxing on your porch, having coffee with friends at the recreation hall, golfing at the adjacent course, walking the park grounds or shopping in downtown Dade City. We also welcome vacationing families and overnight guests on their way in and out of town.
Activities
We offer an on-site driving range and a place to play bocce ball or corn hole. The Park Association puts on many activities during the year, including weekly social golf tournaments, weekly bingo and poker and monthly dances. There are also shuffleboard courts, horseshoe rings, a pool table and a swimming pool.
We offer a wide variety of amenities for our guests. Every single one is serviced regularly and ready for use.
